problem_data.description:
Write a function that takes a list of ints as a parameter
and returns a dictionary containing the counts of
the number of times each value occurs (keys are the number
and the values are the counts)
For example:
<pre>
    countNums([1,2,3,1,2,4]) => {1:2, 2:2, 3:1, 4:1}
    countNums([1,2,3,1,1,2,1]) => {1:4, 2:2, 3:1}
    countNums([78]) => {78:1}
</pre>
